         <abstract>
            <p>It is shown that as m tends to infinity, the error in the integration of the Chebyshev polynomial of the first kind, T&lt;sub&gt;4m+2)j± 2l&lt;/sub&gt;(x), by an m-point Gauss integration rule approaches (-1)&lt;sup&gt;j&lt;/sup&gt; · 2/(4l&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; - 1), l = 0, 1, ⋯, m - 1, and (-1)&lt;sup&gt;j&lt;/sup&gt; · π/2, l = m, for all j.</p>
          </abstract>
